<HEADLINE>
Vasco beats Sport Recife 4-0 in Brazilian League
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 10 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Rio's Vasco beat Pernambuco state's Sport Recife 4-0 in the tenth
round of the Brazilian League on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Vasco reached the seventh place in the
championship, with 14 points.
</P>
<P>
Sport fell two positions, and is now in 16th place, one position
from the relegation zone. In the Brazilian League, the last four
teams are relegated to the second division.
</P>
<P>
Sport had the best moves in the beginning of the game, but Vasco,
in the first home match under new president Roberto Dinamite, got
better opportunities to score before the 35-minute goal by
midfielder Morais assisted by Edmundo.
</P>
<P>
After the end of the first half, Vasco head coach Antonio Lopes
and Sport physical coach Eduardo Baptista had an argument and
were both dismissed from the match by referee Antonio Hora Filho.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Sport came with a bolder attitude, but Vasco
kept the game under control. After getting rid of three Sport's
defenders, Pablo scored his first goal in Vasco's first team.
</P>
<P>
Sport's team became more nervous and started making mistakes as
22 minutes after interval Jean received a pass from Wagner Diniz,
and scored for Vasco.
</P>
<P>
The fourth and last goal from Rio's team was scored by captain
Edmundo, in the 25th minute.
</P>
